<h2>Colt Express</h2>

<h3>Setup</h3>
<ul>
	<li>Base Game
		<ul>
			<li>face-down $250 purse.</li>
			<li>Use N train cars.</li>
			<li>Place Marshal and strongbox in locomotive.</li>
			<li>13 neutral bullet cards.</li>
		</ul>
	</li>
	<li>Horses and Stagecoach
		<ul>
			<li>Stagecoach aligned with locomotive.</li>
			<li>Place Strongbox on stagecoach roof, Shotgun on top of strongbox.</li>
			<li>Place a face-down flask in each car, except locomotive.</li>
			<li>Draw and display (N-1) hostage cards.</li>
			<li>16 neutral bullet cards.</li>
			<li>Horse Attack for starting locations, cannot be locomotive or stagecoach.</li>
		</ul>
	</li>
	<li>Marshal and Prisoners
		<ul>
			<li>Remove Marshal cards from bandit decks.</li>
			<li>Add Brilliant Idea cards to bandit decks.</li>
			<li>Display wanted poster face up for each bandit.</li>
			<li>Brawler cards: gold on top.</li>
			<li>Marshal gets 2 stacks of 6 bullet cards.</li>
			<li>Return arrest warrants of unused bandits.</li>
			<li>2 or 3 bandits: return "Full of Lead" and "Arch Enemy" special target cards.</li>
			<li>Draw 2 arrest warrants and 3 special target cards, without looking, to make a Marshal goal zone.</li>
			<li>2-4 bandits: 4 cars + prison.</li>
			<li>5+ bandits: 5 cars + prison.</li>
			<li>Instead of strongbox, put both mailbags in locomotive.</li>
			<li>Draw 3 prisoner cards, regardless of player count.</li>
		</ul>
	</li>
</ul>


<h3>Victory</h3>
<ul>
	<li>Marshal wins by completing 4 goals.</li>
	<li>Otherwise, richest bandit wins
		<ul>
			<li>Loot</li>
			<li>Gunslinger prize: bandit who shot the most
				<ul>
					<li>all tied players receive $1000</li>
				</ul>
			</li>
			<li>Wanted poster: if Marshal never captured you</li>
			<li>Prisoner: if you still have card</li>
			<li>Hostage's ransom</li>
			<li>Brawler prizes</li>
			<li>Station card effects</li>
		</ul>
	</li>
	<li>Tie: player who received fewest bullet cards from players and events</li>
</ul>

<br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />

